The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, April 30, 2004 				 Stars sing amp; dance for BJP
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, April 29: BJPs Bollywood stars will finally be doing what they are good at: Perform on stage.																								They have had a show in Hyderabad and one is scheduled to be held in Jaipur this evening while another has been planned in Delhi. About a dozen such functions have been organised, said a party functionary. 																								The BJP calls these shows Mahashakti Bharat Sangeet Sandhya. Actor Suresh Oberoi will compere the Delhi show that will not only have some good music but also a heavy dose of the BJPs campaign lines. The songs, he said, would not be the Kaanta laga variety but sober.																								The starry line-up includes Shatrughan Sinha, Vinod Khanna, Dara Singh, Hema Malini, Jeetendra, Poonam Dhillon, Smriti Irani, Sudha Chandran and Mukesh Khanna. 
